               LONDON;
Printed for the Booksellers of London
and Westminster. 1700.

sp.p:
It is indeed, a Laborious Work;
for besides Compiling of so many Volumes;
the great Correspondence which I am obliged
to keep, is no small trouble.

Truly that was a great Oversight;
it would have given much Satisfaction to
the Learned World, had my Lord Darcy confirmed it.

Nay, enough of all Conscience;


I find no fault with that; but I find no Philosophy
in it.
